name: Burying The Line After A Long Walk
description:
Here's the start of something a little different for me. I've been looking to produce a few more conceptual artworks, away from my commercial illustration work.
I won't offer any spoilers as to what the work is about as the enjoyment comes in developing your own interpretations. If you are curious though, send me a tweet @robinboyden and we can discuss.

Giclée print on A3 Archival Matte paper (with white border) for a limited time only.

Signed by the artist.

name: Yourself And Another Rhythm
description:
Here's the start of something a little different for me. I've been looking to produce a few more conceptual artworks, away from my commercial illustration work and this is the first of a few.
  I won't offer any spoilers as to what the work is about as the enjoyment comes in developing your own interpretations. If you are curious though, send me a tweet @robinboyden and we can discuss.


Giclée print on A3 Archival Matte paper (with white border) for a limited time only.

Signed by the artist.

name: Accurate Scientific Dinosaur Print
description:
Say hello to Raary the dinosaur, and learn a little Latin at the same time (that's a lie) with this jolly new print.

Giclée print on A3 Archival Matte paper (with white border) for a limited time only.

Signed by the artist.

name: The Night Draws In - Sundance
description:
You can now stare at this creation, the latest print from The Night Draws In range by Robin Boyden, on your wall. This illustration was produced exclusively for the Inkygoodness Totem Homecoming show in Birmingham in July 2011.

High quality giclee print, signed by the artist, comes with fancy packaging and usually a secret treat inside too. (420mm x 297mm)

name: Manhattan Map
description:
As seen in Computer Arts Projects July 2011 Issue. 

A great souvenir for fans of one of the most vibrant cities on Earth.

Giclée print on A3 Archival Matte paper (with white border) for a limited time only.

Signed by the artist.
